str2: A primary particle; but, and, etc.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A ruler of angels, a superior angel, an archangel. From archo and aggelos; a chief angel.
Michael, an archangel. Of Hebrew origin; Michael, an archangel.
When, at which time. From hos and te; at which too, i.e. When.

str2: From dia and krino; to separate thoroughly, i.e. to withdraw from, or oppose; figuratively, to discriminate, or hesitate.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
From diaballo; a traducer; specially, Satan.
From the base of peran; properly, through, i.e. Around; figuratively with respect to; used in various applications, of place, cause or time.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Body, flesh; the body of the Church. From sozo; the body, used in a very wide application, literally or figuratively.
Or Moses, or Mouses of Hebrew origin; Moseus, Moses, or Mouses, the Hebrew lawgiver.

str2: To dare, endure, be bold, have courage, make up the mind. From tolma; to venture; by implication, to be courageous.
To bring forward (against), impose, inflict. From epi and phero; to bear upon, i.e. Adduce (accuse, inflict), superinduce.
Abusive or scurrilous language, blasphemy. From blasphemos; vilification.
Decision; by extension, a tribunal; by implication, justice.
But, except, however. Neuter plural of allos; properly, other things, i.e. contrariwise.

str2: Answer, bid, bring word, command. A primary verb; to speak or say.
Lord, master, sir; the Lord. From kuros; supreme in authority, i.e. controller; by implication, Master.

str2: From epi and timao; to tax upon, i.e. Censure or admonish; by implication, forbid.

str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
